The paper presents a state estimator for robot ego-motion using lidar and IMU sensors, which is a common problem in robotics and falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of lidar also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a possible sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel formulation for the state estimator, which involves iterative error-state Kalman filtering, indicating machine learning (cs.LG) as another possible sub-category. The use of sensors and estimation techniques also suggests control systems (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method compared to state-of-the-art algorithms, indicating artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a possible sub-category.
